{title: Beautiful Texas}
{artist: Hank Thompson}
{composer: Written by Wilbert Lee O'Daniels}

[C]We've all read of the beautiful stories
Of the countries far over the [G7]sea
From whence came our ancestors
To establish this land of the [C]free
There are some folks who still like to travel
To [C7]see what they have over [F]there
But when they go look it's [C]not like the book
And [D7]they see there is [G7]none to com[C]pare
To beautiful beautiful Texas
Where the beautiful bluebonnets [G7]grow
We're proud of our forefathers
Who fought at the Ala[C]mo
You can live on the plains or the mountains
Or [C7]down where the sea breezes [F]blow
But you're still in beautiful [C]Texas
The [D7]most beautiful [G7]place that I [C]know
You can travel on beautiful highways
By cities by village by [G7]farms
Or fly above on the skyways
To the beauty below you will [C]charm
White cotton green pastures blue rivers
Golden [C7]wheat fields and fruit trees that [F]bear
You may search till doomsday [C]and then you will say
That [D7]Texas has [G7]beauty to [C]spare
Repeat # 3,4  Oh beautiful...